// Complete Bipartite Graph K(m,n)
// m = vertices in first partition
// n = vertices in second partition

FUNCTION countEdgesKmn(m, n)
 // In complete bipartite, every vertex in first set
 // connects to every vertex in second set

 edges = m * n
 RETURN edges

// Example:
// K(4,3) has 4 * 3 = 12 edges
// K(1,5) has 1 * 5 = 5 edges (star graph)
